<li id="cite_note-225"><b><a href="#cite_ref-225" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFAhmad2007">Ahmad, Ahmad Atif (2007), "<i>Authority, Conflict, and the Transmission of Diversity in Medieval Islamic Law</i> by R. Kevin Jaques", <i>Journal of Islamic Studies</i> <b>18=issue=2</b>: 246–248 [246], <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1093%2Fjis%2Fetm005" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1093%2Fjis%2Fetm005" rel="nofollow">10.1093/jis/etm005</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=%27%27Authority%2C+Conflict%2C+and+the+Transmission+of+Diversity+in+Medieval+Islamic+Law%27%27+by+R.+Kevin+Jaques&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Islamic+Studies&amp;rft.aulast=Ahmad&amp;rft.aufirst=Ahmad+Atif&amp;rft.au=Ahmad%2C+Ahmad+Atif&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.volume=18%3Dissue%3D2&amp;rft.pages=246%E2%80%93248+%5B246%5D&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1093%2Fjis%2Fetm005&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Islamic_Golden_Age"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-226"><b><a href="#cite_ref-226" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F01E0D71139F93BA35752C1A9679C8B63" class="external text" title="http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F01E0D71139F93BA35752C1A9679C8B63" rel="nofollow">Economic Scene; The decline of the Muslim Middle East, and the roots of resentment, can be traced to Islamic inheritance law.</a>, New York Times</li>
<li id="cite_note-227"><b><a href="#cite_ref-227" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.ncpa.org/iss/int/pd110801a.html" class="external text" title="http://www.ncpa.org/iss/int/pd110801a.html" rel="nofollow">How Islamic Inheritance Law Impeded Development</a>, National Center for Policy Analysis</li>
<li id="cite_note-228"><b><a href="#cite_ref-228" title="">^</a></b> David A. King, "The Astronomy of the Mamluks", <i>Isis</i>, 74 (1983):531-555</li>
<li id="cite_note-229"><b><a href="#cite_ref-229" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/George_Saliba" title="George Saliba">George Saliba</a>, "Writing the History of Arabic Astronomy: Problems and Differing Perspectives (Review Article), <i>Journal of the American Oriental Society</i>, 116 (1996): 709-718.</li>
</ol>
